<li id="cite_note-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39" title="">^</a></b> ‘The south (of India) was then vigorously creative in producing Mahayana Sutras’ – AK Warder, Indian Buddhism, 3rd edition, 1999, p. 335.</li>
