<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> <i>There are, it seems, very few things that can be said with certainty about Mahayana Buddhism</i>, Macmillan Encyclopedia of Buddhism, 2004, page 492</li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53" title="">^</a></b> <i>But apart from the fact that it can be said with some certainty that the Buddhism embedded in China, Korea, Tibet, and Japan is Mahayana Buddhism, it is no longer clear what else can be said with certainty about Mahayana Buddhism itself, and especially about its earlier, and presumably formative, period in India.</i>, Macmillan Encyclopedia of Buddhism, 2004, page 492</li>
